    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='Based on the provided excerpts, here is a summary of what management says about the AI segment\'s investment timeline, path to profitability, capital expenditure plans, and maturity stage:\n\n### Investment Timeline & Maturity Stage\n*   **Early Stage & Significant Losses:** Management explicitly states the AI segment is in an "earlier stage of development" and has a "relatively early stage" business. It has incurred "significant operating losses since inception."\n*   **Multi-Year Investment Horizon:** The company repeatedly emphasizes a **"multi-year investment horizon"** before large-scale AI infrastructure investments (like the COLOSSUS data centers) translate into "sustained positive AI Segment Adjusted EBITDA." Profitability is not expected in the near term.\n\n### Path to Profitability\n*   **Uncertain and Not Guaranteed:** Management cautions that "we may not achieve profitability in this segment, or, if achieved, sustain it." There is "no assurance that the returns on our AI investments will be adequate to justify the capital deployed."\n*   **Contingent on Market Adoption:** The path to profitability depends on the degree to which AI products and services "prove to be broadly useful in real-world applications," which is currently "uncertain." The "commercial value proposition of frontier AI models remains largely unproven."\n*   **Overarching Strategy:** The company is prioritizing "execution speed, capacity expansion, and technological leadership over near‑term margin optimization," believing this maximizes long-term value.\n\n### Capital Expenditure Plans\n*   **Massive and Accelerating:** AI capital expenditures have grown explosively, from **$463 million in 2023 to $12.7 billion in 2025**. Management expects these costs "to continue to increase for the foreseeable future."\n*   **Infrastructure-Driven:** The spending is primarily for "specialized computing hardware, data center infrastructure, energy procurement, and technical personnel."\n*   **Plans to Scale Further:** The company intends to "allocate substantial capital to build our AI compute infrastructure" and plans to access various financing solutions to fund future growth.\n\n### Key Forward-Looking Statements on Infrastructure\n*   **COLOSSUS Data Centers:** Management highlights the rapid, cost-effective deployment of the **COLOSSUS and COLOSSUS II** facilities as a core competitive advantage, bringing them online in 122 and 91 days respectively, at costs "considerably lower than industry benchmarks."\n*   **Orbital AI Compute:** A forward-looking vision is introduced to move "power-intensive AI workloads into orbit" using solar energy. This is presented as a future strategic initiative to overcome terrestrial energy constraints, leveraging the company\'s launch capabilities.\n\nIn summary, management\'s message is that the AI segment is a **capital-intensive, long-term bet** currently in its investment phase with no near-term profitability in sight. Success depends on the uncertain broad adoption of AI and the continued effectiveness of massive, rapid infrastructure scaling.',
